      • contactProbe

        public Location contactProbe(boolean forward,
                             Length contactProbeDepthZ)
                      throws java.lang.Exception
        Z-Probe this Nozzle for contact underneath the current location. When forward is true, the nozzle probes for contact and stops when contact is made. The current machine position determines the effective contact location. When forward is false, the nozzle retracts from probing (if needed).
        Parameters:
        forward -
        Returns:
        The probed location.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
